2. I stopped being so restrictive. 
.
Hear me out… it was hard to realize that this was even possible. Having tried all kids of “diets” and exercising like crazy I still wasn’t happy.  And I would constantly be craving something.  I would either not be happy or I would overeat the foods I was “allowed to eat” …Now Keto was fun for a little while and I came up with all kinds of fun ideas that were inspired by real food for me…. But inspired by real food wasn’t what I wanted. I wanted the real thing.  Keto helped me get to a place of moderation and intuitive eating so I could know that I don’t need to binge in order to be happy. Having the foods I want in moderation and not using words like “allowed to” when pertaining to food has changed my whole outlook. Sometimes I catch myself going back to that mindset and getting down on myself if I feel like I’ve gained weight or ate something “bad” but then I remind myself I am SO much more happy with myself knowing I have control over my relationship with food and it doesn’t have control over me. 
I’m not a doctor or dietician but I am constantly working on myself, and my physical & mental health. Keto may be great for you. Other diets may be great for you. I just found what makes me tick and wanted to share.  How about you?  What’s your relationship with food like and how did you get there? I want to hear some other ways people achieve this and hopefully it can help others!
